{"type":"message","id":"cf75adea","parentId":"3c6e24e4","timestamp":"2026-04-14T11:14:31.728Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the current sessions and compare against the heartbeat state.\n\n**Current sessions (from sessions_list at 11:14 UTC):**\n1. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — running — this cron, 11:14 UTC\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — running — updated 11:12 UTC\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` — running — updated 11:05 UTC\n\n\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258` — session ended at 10:43 UTC with a 5p update delivered\n5. `agent:master-orchestrator:main` — heartbeat session wrapped up at 10:41 UTC\n6. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` — done at 10:42 UTC\n\nLooking back at the previous run from 11:12 UTC, I'm seeing the same core sessions active then — the cron jobs were running with their timestamps, and that QLHV group session had already ended by that point. So the current state at 11:14 is essentially unchanged from just two minutes ago.\n\nBut wait, I'm noticing something important: the `cron:6f3323ef` session that was marked as ended at 10:39 in the 11:05 heartbeat is actually showing as running in the current session list. This session is still active, which means either the 11:05 state was wrong about it being ended, or it restarted after being marked as done.\n\nComparing across all the heartbeat data, the active sessions have remained consistent — the main cron job and the two sub-crons are all running across every check. The QLHV group session ended at 10:43 and hasn't restarted, so that's still concluded. Nothing new has failed or changed, so there's no report to send. I'm noticing the cron session for ac986a8d that was stuck has disappeared from the current list — it looks like it either ended normally or the system cleaned it up after the delivery failure, which is a positive sign that the Telegram gateway issue has resolved itself.","thinkingSignature":"6043bdeff30026eacac435ef5fb4cca15eb0114999edce0cd38cc4f2705548b8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t96f89xzh2hd_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":9614,"output":557,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":435,"totalTokens":24550,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776165258493,"responseId":"062d548b420925120397e43f46c168f6"}}
